<doc id="1243264" wikidata="Q1019448" url="?curid=1243264" title="Vogar">
<text>Vogar () is a small town in the southwest of Iceland. It is the seat of the municipality of Vogar (Sveitarfélagið Vogar). There is a highly automated atmospheric gas extraction plant in the town, with the oxygen produced being the only local source for Iceland&#x27;s healthcare use. The town also has a fish roe incubation centre for Atlantic salmon.

==Overview==
The population of the municipality of Vogar was almost 1400 as of 2023.
