<doc id="1243297" wikidata="Q203649" url="?curid=1243297" title="Callicebus">
<text>Callicebus is a genus of monkeys known as titi monkeys.

Historically, titis were monogeneric, comprising only the genus &quot;Callicebus&quot; . Owing to the great diversity found across titi monkey species, a new genus-level taxonomy was recently proposed that recognises three genera within the subfamily Callicebinae; &quot;Cheracebus&quot; for the species of the &quot;torquatus&quot; group (Widow titis); &quot;Plecturocebus&quot; for the Amazonian and Chaco titis of the &quot;moloch&quot; and &quot;donacophilus&quot; groups; and &quot;Callicebus&quot; &quot;sensu stricto&quot;, for species of the Atlantic Forest &quot;personatus&quot; group.

In 2014, a previously unknown orange &quot;Callicebus&quot; was spotted in the Peruvian Amazon; it has not been determined whether this constitutes a color variant or a new species.

==Species==
There are 5 species in this genus:
*Barbara Brown&#x27;s titi monkey, &quot;Callicebus barbarabrownae&quot;
* Coimbra Filho&#x27;s titi monkey, &quot;Callicebus coimbrai&quot;
* Coastal black-handed titi monkey, &quot;Callicebus melanochir&quot;
* Black-fronted titi monkey, &quot;Callicebus nigrifrons&quot;
* Atlantic titi monkey, &quot;Callicebus personatus&quot;
